Package: fedregs
Type: Package
Title: A Package to Facilitate Text Analysis of the US Code of Federal Regulations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Scott", "Large", email = "scott.large@noaa.gov", role = c("cre", "aut"))
Description: The Code of Federal Regulations (CFR) annual edition is the codification 
    of the general and permanent rules published in the Federal Register by the departments
    and agencies of the Federal Government of the United States of America. Simply, the 
    fedregs package facilitates word processing and sentiment analysis of the CFR using tidy principles.
License: GPL 3.0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0),
    magrittr (>= 1.5)
Imports: dplyr (>= 0.7.4),
    xml2 (>= 1.2.0),
    purrr(>= 0.2.5),
    rvest(>= 0.3.2),
    stringi(>= 1.1.7),
    httr (>= 1.3.1)
Suggests: 
    ggplot2 (>= 2.2.1),
    tidyr (>= 0.8.0),
    testthat (>= 2.0.0)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
